snippet.textDisplay: I feel like Colin doesn’t want to talk about how ineffective the Patriots have looked playing good teams. The only quality win they have this season is against a Buffalo team who also hasn’t played anybody. I think it’s time to admit that after three straight super bowl appearances that the Pats are gassed and Brady looks old. Having to go on the road and beat The Ravens at home is going to be tough and I honestly don’t see anybody doing it with the run game they have. No the Pats dynasty isn’t over but they aren’t as good as everyone thinks and they are definitely not as good as the other top teams in the AFC
